<span id="freeTextContainer5021438908233425701">Good. First read it in 2002. Listened to an audio version of it narrated by Max McLean in 2015. That was good too. McLean&apos;s reading is good, although it sometimes borders on creepy. The Puritans represented are really solid. Their prayers sometimes veered into the predictably puritanical introspection, but there were many glorious stretches where they were doing nothing of the kind. There were many edifying phrases. </span>
